SIMPLE: somewhat
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Somewhat
<hw>Some"what`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>More or
less; a certain quantity or degree; a part, more or less;
something.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>These salts have <qex>somewhat</qex> of a nitrous taste.</q>
<rj><qau>Grew.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Somewhat</qex> of his good sense will suffer, in this
transfusion, and much of the beauty of his thoughts will be lost.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A person or thing of importance; a
somebody.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Here come those that worship me.⟦br⟧
They think that I am <qex>somewhat</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Somewhat</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Somewhat
<hw>Some"what`</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In some degree or measure; a
little.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His giantship is gone, <qex>somewhat</qex> crestfallen.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Somewhat</qex> back from the village street.</q>
<rj><qau>Longfellow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Somewhen</ent>⟦br⟧
